---
description: Enforce frontend specialist delegation for UI work
alwaysApply: false
globs:
  - "**/*.{tsx,jsx,css,scss}"
  - "**/components/**"
  - "**/routes/**"
  - "**/pages/**"
---

When frontend or UI surfaces are touched, delegate to matching frontend specialists before implementation for **L2+** tasks. Full matrix: [.cursor/docs/orchestration-routing.md](.cursor/docs/orchestration-routing.md).

- page composition, forms, tables, admin UX -> `frontend-architecture-agent`
- shared UI component APIs and reusable primitives -> `design-system-agent`
- accessibility/responsive concerns -> `ux-accessibility-agent` or `responsive-accessibility-auditor`

If shared UI or token conventions are changed, include:

- `design-system-guardian` for governance updates
- `design-token-auditor` when token/class normalization is involved

Do not finalize L2+ UI work without a frontend specialist summary and verification coverage rationale.
